headline: 3 Reasons Investors Watch Stryker (SYK)
summary: Over the past six months, Stryker’s shares (currently trading at $350.50) have posted a disappointing 9% loss, well below the S&P 500’s 13.4% gain. This may have investors wondering how to approach the situation.

headline: Stryker (SYK) Leadership Shake-Up: Evaluating the Stock’s Valuation After New President and COO Appointment
summary: Stryker (SYK) just reshuffled its leadership deck, naming long time insider Spencer Stiles as future President and COO while elevating Dylan Crotty to lead Orthopaedics, and investors are rightly asking what this means for the stock.
